SIMPLE: undevil
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Undevil
<hw>Un*dev"il</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>devil</ets>.]</ety> <def>To free from possession
by a devil or evil spirit; to exorcise.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They boy having gotten a habit of counterfeiting . . . would not
be <qex>undeviled</qex> by all their exorcisms.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Undevotion</ent>⟦br⟧
